0:13:48.935,000 --> 0:13:49,000
We need Republicans as well.

248
0:13:50.464,000 --> 0:13:52,000
This used to be a bipartisan issue,

249
0:13:52.497,000 --> 0:13:54,000
and I know that in this group it really is.

250
0:13:54.978,000 --> 0:13:55,000
Become politically active.

251
0:13:56.554,000 --> 0:13:58,000
Make our democracy work the way it's supposed to work.

252
0:13:59.753,000 --> 0:14:04,000
Support the idea of capping carbon dioxide emissions --

253
0:14:05.326,000 --> 0:14:07,000
global warming pollution -- and trading it.

254
0:14:07.365,000 --> 0:14:11,000
Here's why: as long as the United States is out of the world system,

255
0:14:12,000 --> 0:14:13,000
it's not a closed system.

256
0:14:13.692,000 --> 0:14:17,000
Once it becomes a closed system, with U.S. participation,

257
0:14:17.763,000 --> 0:14:19,000
then everybody who's on a board of directors --

258
0:14:20.01,000 --> 0:14:22,000
how many people here serve on the board of directors

259
0:14:23.023,000 --> 0:14:24,000
of a corporation?

260
0:14:25.415,000 --> 0:14:26,000
Once it's a closed system,

261
0:14:26.865,000 --> 0:14:32,000
you will have legal liability if you do not urge your CEO

262
0:14:33.126,000 --> 0:14:37,000
to get the maximum income from reducing and trading the carbon emissions

263
0:14:37.277,000 --> 0:14:38,000
that can be avoided.

264
0:14:38.61,000 --> 0:14:4,000
The market will work to solve this problem --

265
0:14:43.949,000 --> 0:14:45,000
